content: |
  ---
  name: merch-report-pdf
  description: Assemble the end-of-quarter markdown review into a one-page, shareable PDF for the regional team. Use last, after sales-analysis-chart has produced the PNG charts and markdown-optimizer has produced the recommended discounts. The skill generates and runs Python (reportlab) that embeds the charts, a recommendation table, and notes into a PDF. It does not decide anything — it only renders already-confirmed results.
  ---
  <!-- bic:source=upload -->
  # Merchandising Review PDF

  This skill produces the **shareable PDF** that closes out a markdown review. You fill it with
  the **already-confirmed** charts and recommendations, then generate and run a short Python
  (`reportlab`) snippet to render the PDF. Never invent numbers — every value comes from the
  `sales-analysis-chart` and `markdown-optimizer` skills and the Store Policy Agent's guardrails.

  ## When to use

  Use this **last**, once:

  - the charts (`top_sellers.png`, `slow_movers.png`, optionally `markdowns.png`) are rendered,
  - the promo recommendations are final (from `markdown-optimizer`),
  - the manager has confirmed which items to apply (and which to exclude for clearance).

  ## Inputs

  - The chart PNG paths produced earlier.
  - The recommendation rows: `(product, price, discount, new_price, new_margin, action)`.
  - A short notes string (window, guardrail source, any clearance flags).

  ## Generate and run this Python

  ```python
  from reportlab.lib.pagesizes import LETTER
  from reportlab.lib.units import inch
  from reportlab.lib import colors
  from reportlab.platypus import (SimpleDocTemplate, Paragraph, Spacer, Table,
                                  TableStyle, HRFlowable, Image)
  from reportlab.lib.styles import getSampleStyleSheet, ParagraphStyle
  import os

  # --- confirmed values (fill these in) ---
  subtitle = "Store #214 - Seattle | Prepared 2026-06-07 | Window: 8 weeks (2026-04-12 to 2026-05-31)"
  charts = ["top_sellers.png", "slow_movers.png", "markdowns.png"]   # paths from earlier skills
  promo_rows = [
      # (product, price, discount, new price, new margin, action) — only the APPLIED promo set
      ("OmegaVision VR Headset", "$199.99", "-30.0%", "$139.99", "50.0%", "Promo"),
      ("Galaxy Smash", "$49.99", "-30.0%", "$34.99", "48.6%", "Promo"),
      ("BlastBox Cadet Bundle", "$149.99", "-13.7%", "$129.42", "15.0%", "Promo (floor)"),
  ]
  notes = ("Guardrails from Store Policy Agent (promo): max 30% off, 15% margin floor. "
           "EXCLUDED - BlastBox Omega Core: only 5.9% discount possible under the floor and no "
           "inbound PO (16 weeks in stock, phased out by the MEGA Edition); recommended for "
           "separate CLEARANCE with manager flag, not this promo.")

  styles = getSampleStyleSheet()
  h1 = ParagraphStyle("h1", parent=styles["Title"], fontSize=17, spaceAfter=4)
  h2 = ParagraphStyle("h2", parent=styles["Heading2"], fontSize=12, spaceBefore=10, spaceAfter=4)
  small = ParagraphStyle("sm", parent=styles["BodyText"], fontSize=8, textColor=colors.grey)
  body = styles["BodyText"]

  doc = SimpleDocTemplate("merch_review.pdf", pagesize=LETTER,
                          topMargin=0.6*inch, bottomMargin=0.6*inch)
  flow = [Paragraph("BlastBox Omega &mdash; End-of-Quarter Markdown Review", h1),
          HRFlowable(width="100%", color=colors.HexColor("#6b2fb5")),
          Paragraph(subtitle, small), Spacer(1, 4),
          Paragraph("Performance charts", h2)]
  for c in charts[:2]:
      if os.path.exists(c):
          flow.append(Image(c, width=5.2*inch, height=2.97*inch))

  flow.append(Paragraph("Recommended promo markdowns", h2))
  data = [["Product", "Price", "Discount", "New price", "New margin", "Action"]] + [list(r) for r in promo_rows]
  t = Table(data, colWidths=[1.9*inch, 0.75*inch, 0.85*inch, 0.85*inch, 0.85*inch, 1.1*inch])
  t.setStyle(TableStyle([
      ("BACKGROUND", (0, 0), (-1, 0), colors.HexColor("#6b2fb5")),
      ("TEXTCOLOR", (0, 0), (-1, 0), colors.white),
      ("FONTSIZE", (0, 0), (-1, -1), 8),
      ("GRID", (0, 0), (-1, -1), 0.5, colors.grey),
      ("ROWBACKGROUNDS", (0, 1), (-1, -1), [colors.white, colors.HexColor("#f3eefb")]),
      ("ALIGN", (1, 0), (-1, -1), "CENTER"),
  ]))
  flow.append(t)
  if os.path.exists(charts[2]):
      flow.append(Image(charts[2], width=5.0*inch, height=2.86*inch))
  flow.append(Paragraph("Notes", h2))
  flow.append(Paragraph(notes, body))

  doc.build(flow)
  print("WROTE merch_review.pdf")
  ```

  ## Report

  - Confirm the PDF was written and give its filename.
  - Summarize the promo set applied and any item excluded for clearance.
  - Offer to email or regenerate the report.

  ## Notes

  - Use `reportlab` (the available PDF library). Do not depend on `weasyprint`/`fpdf` or network calls.
  - Escape `&` as `&amp;` in any text passed to `Paragraph`.
  - Keep it to one page; embed the PNGs produced by the earlier skills (do not redraw the charts here).
  - If the chart PNGs are not present in the working directory (e.g. a new turn cleared them),
    re-run `sales-analysis-chart` (and `markdown-optimizer` for `markdowns.png`) first so the
    images exist, then build the PDF.
